Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.67,0:10:19.09,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Right, {\i1}luck.{\i0} {Shuujin says "un" meaning "yes" and the word for "luck" is also "un." If you can think of a better word Shuujin can say that Saikouu can mis-hear as "luck," put that in. It's not significant enough to put a note. Also the sign is like the previous ones.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.34,0:10:20.09,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.05,0:11:39.72,TS,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.39,0:10:23.93,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,What? So in the end it's all about luck...?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.41,0:10:25.77,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.77,0:10:28.35,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're not a genius, you're just a gambler after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.04,0:10:31.67,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,But just talking about dreams won't make them a reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.19,0:10:34.65,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna keep drawing all weekend.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.03,0:10:41.82,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Then I'm gonna read all the manga in this place!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.24,0:10:53.09,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,This "Chichi no Tamashii" is so sad...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.25,0:10:53.09,TL Notes,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,TL note: Chichi no Tamashii = Father's Soul {These are really obscure manga, so I think it's worth putting in a note for what the title means.}
